Anthony John Bates: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 6:03 PM ET
Household Durables

Company Overview of GoPro, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Anthony John Bates  Director, GoPro, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 14 different industries.See Board Relationships50$12,750,120As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Anthony John Bates, also known as Tony, served as the President of GoPro, Inc. from June 2014 to December 31, 2016. Mr. Bates served as an Executive Vice President of Business Development and Evangelism at Microsoft Corporation from July 2013 to March 2014. He has more than 25 years of experience in the telecommunications and Internet industry and has played a major role in shaping and growing the Internet. He joined Microsoft in 2011. He served as Vice President ... and General Manager of the high-end router business since July 2000. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Skype Technologies, S.A. since October 31, 2010 and served as its President. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Skype Global S.à r.l. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Skype Limited since October 2010 and its President. He served as the President of Skype Communications Division at Microsoft Corporation from 2011 to July 2013. From 1996 to October 2010, he served in various roles at Cisco Systems, Inc. He served as Senior Vice President and General Manager of Service Provider Routing Technology Group at Cisco Systems, Inc. and also served as its Senior Vice President of Carrier Core & Multiservices Business Unit from July 2005 to 2010, Vice President of Carrier Core Multiservice Business Unit from July 2004 to July 2005 and General Manager of Service Provider Group until 2010. He was responsible for the strategy and execution of Cisco's High End Router (CRS-1 and the Cisco 12000) and Multi-Service WAN (MGX) product lines. He served as Senior Vice President and General Manager of Cisco's Enterprise, Commercial and Small Business Group. He directed the backbone-engineering strategy for Internet. He joined Cisco in 1996. He served as an Adviser of TokBox Inc. During his tenure, he also served as Director of Marketing for the Optical Internetworking Business Unit of Cisco, Manager of Engineering for Internet POP Systems (IPSBU) and Technical Leader in the Office of the Chief Technology Officer. He served as Backbone Engineering Manager for Internet Backbone Group at MCI, where he drove the backbone engineering strategy for Internet MCI. He has been an Independent Director at eBay Inc. since March 2015, VMware, Inc. since February 8, 2016, SIRIUS XM Radio Inc. since September 9, 2013, GoPro, Inc. since June 2014 and Tipping Point Community since June 2012. He serves as a Director of Bubbly Inc. He served as a Director of Big Switch Networks Inc. He served as a Director of Sirius XM Holdings Inc. from September 2013 to February 19, 2016. He served as a Director of TokBox Inc. He serves as a Co-Chairman of number of councils and initiatives, Chief among them the Service Provider Business Council and the Cisco Development Council. He served on the Boards of YouTube and LOVEFiLM. He has published +IETF RFCs in the areas of Internet Routing and Operations. Mr. Bates also holds seven patents in related layer 2 and layer 3 innovations.Read Full Background




