DID YOU KNOW?



Businesses in Australia that are considering a merger should contact the Australian Competition & Consumer Commission when the mergers seems as though it might legitimately happen. The ACCC will review the merger to make sure it does not break any of the rules of s.50 of the Competition and Consumer Act.

















